narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I developed many skills in computer programming, theoretical mathematics, and econometrics. Through out this course I had to thoroughly understand and alter other professors code to reach a certain objective as well as apply the algorithm we developed to other academic papers and analyze the validity of these approaches. I am leaving this class with confidence and experience in preforming economic research.
This is great if you have a project you want to do with a professor you want to do it with.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The strengths of this course would have to be the extremely interesting material and the loose course structure that allowed me to explore and create. I would also like to note that there was a lot of interaction between Professor Arkolakis, Fabian Eckert (the grad student I worked with), and me. I never felt lost and these two were always there to help and guide me. Because I got to work with such amazing passionate people and I made the most of the experience I can't really think of any weaknesses.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would definitely recommend this course to someone with an idea for a research project and with supportive professors and grad students to work with.
